44
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:17,488
or even do the funky chicken.

45
00:03:18,072 --> 00:03:19,324
I am curious.

46
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:21,910
I'd like to see that.

47
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,927
I thought you liked rough hands.

48
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,931
I just wanted to get a good look

49
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:45,141
to see if our baby's hands
will resemble yours.

50
00:03:47,435 --> 00:03:49,270
Then I should show you my feet too.

51
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,655
I love you.

52
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:03,159
I said, I love you.

53
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:13,044
I wanted to tell you last time,

54
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:16,047
but the words just didn't come out.

55
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,298
Thank you.

56
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:20,802
I heard most men are embarrassed
to say that.

57
00:04:20,885 --> 00:04:22,512
But it's the truth.

58
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:24,597
They're embarrassed
because they don't mean it.

59
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:30,019
What about you? Do you love me?

60
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:34,023
There are times

61
00:04:35,024 --> 00:04:38,278
when you can feel their love
but still want confirmation.

62
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,196
I'll think of you often.

63
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:42,991
Perhaps, always.

64
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:46,744
When I go to bed and when I wake up.

65
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,665
Let's decide on a time.

66
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:54,168
When we go to bed and when we wake up…

67
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:58,131
Then maybe we might be able
to read each other's thoughts

68
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,591
with our hearts.

69
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,232
I can't feel anything right now.

70
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,693
That's because I'm right in front of you.

71
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:23,531
Can I sit beside you?

72
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,621
I want to sit next to you today.

73
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,417
If I could,

74
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,128
I'd treat her to a delicious meal
right now.

75
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:40,965
I hope she'll safely carry
our precious grandchild.

76
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:43,468
-Mr. Kim.
-Yes, sir?

77
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:46,679
-Do you argue with your wife?
-Of course, sir.

78
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:49,557
-How do you reconcile?
-I let it run its course.

79
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,018
The old saying is true.

80
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:56,230
They say couples should always sleep
in the same bed even after a fight.

81
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:57,982
That's right.

82
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:01,027
What a shame that we sleep
in separate beds.

83
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:07,283
You must have visited China often.

84
